i## title: Poisoning LLM web scrapers	/	tilde.team	70
i## date: "2025-11-01"	/	tilde.team	70
i	/	tilde.team	70
i## Introduction	/	tilde.team	70
i	/	tilde.team	70
iAll servers available on the Internet are exposed to	/	tilde.team	70
iattacks, scraping, open port scanning, vulnerability	/	tilde.team	70
iscanning by services, DDoS, etc. What interests me today are	/	tilde.team	70
irobots that download web page content without permission.	/	tilde.team	70
i	/	tilde.team	70
iI consulted the logs of my web server managed by NGINX using	/	tilde.team	70
ia visual generated by the goaccess tool. The majority of	/	tilde.team	70
iHTTP requests come from unknown web browsers and crawlers.	/	tilde.team	70
iKnowing that unidentified browsers are also crawlers. The	/	tilde.team	70
iimages below show that on October 30, 2025, there were	/	tilde.team	70
i59,454 HTTP requests from crawlers.	/	tilde.team	70
hgoaccess	URL:https://goaccess.io/	goaccess.io	443
i	/	tilde.team	70
i/goaccess_web_browsers.png	/	tilde.team	70
I/goaccess_web_browsers.png	/~nagi/goaccess_web_browsers.png	tilde.team	70
i	/	tilde.team	70
i/goaccess_web_browsers_crawlers.png	/	tilde.team	70
I/goaccess_web_browsers_crawlers.png	/~nagi/goaccess_web_browsers_crawlers.png	tilde.team	70
i	/	tilde.team	70
iMost of these crawlers have questionable ethics, and they	/	tilde.team	70
ialso pollute the server's storage space and add extra	/	tilde.team	70
iworkload to the processor.	/	tilde.team	70
i	/	tilde.team	70
i## An aggressive solution	/	tilde.team	70
i	/	tilde.team	70
iTo counter these robots, I researched existing solutions. I	/	tilde.team	70
ithen found a post Mastodon post that lists free, open-source	/	tilde.team	70
itools on the tldr.nettime.org instance. The common goal of	/	tilde.team	70
ithese tools is to sabotage AIs.	/	tilde.team	70
hpost	URL:https://tldr.nettime.org/@asrg/113867412641585520	tldr.nettime.org	443
htldr.nettime.org	URL:https://tldr.nettime.org	tldr.nettime.org	443
i	/	tilde.team	70
iAmong them, I chose an aggressive solution called iocaine.	/	tilde.team	70
iIt is a web server that generates a page containing garbage	/	tilde.team	70
itext, and within that text there are links to new pages, and	/	tilde.team	70
iso on. It is a kind of infinite maze in which robots will	/	tilde.team	70
iget lost.	/	tilde.team	70
hiocaine	URL:https://iocaine.madhouse-project.org/	iocaine.madhouse-project.org	443
i	/	tilde.team	70
i## Filtering non-human visitors	/	tilde.team	70
i	/	tilde.team	70
iThe aim is to redirect robots to iocaine. To do this, we	/	tilde.team	70
ifirst need to be able to identify them. For this, I took	/	tilde.team	70
iinspiration from the ai.robots.txt project, which provides a	/	tilde.team	70
ilist of IAs and robots to block. The project provides	/	tilde.team	70
iexamples of NGINX configurations, which I have adapted for	/	tilde.team	70
imy needs. I also used a list of IP address ranges that	/	tilde.team	70
icorrespond to Facebook web crawlers.	/	tilde.team	70
hiocaine	URL:https://iocaine.madhouse-project.org/	iocaine.madhouse-project.org	443
hai.robots.txt	URL:https://github.com/ai-robots-txt/ai.robots.txt	github.com	443
i	/	tilde.team	70
iI'd like to thank Agate Blue for writing an extremely	/	tilde.team	70
idetailed article on iocaine and its implementation with	/	tilde.team	70
iNGINX. I was inspired by some of his configurations.	/	tilde.team	70
hAgate Blue	URL:https://agate.blue	agate.blue	443
harticle	URL:https://agate.blue/2025/03/27/Pi%C3%A9ger-les-robots-d'indexation-gr%C3%A2ce-%C3%A0-nginx-et-iocaine.html#detect-robots-with-nginx	agate.blue	443
hiocaine	URL:https://iocaine.madhouse-project.org/	iocaine.madhouse-project.org	443
i	/	tilde.team	70
iI ended up with a reverse proxy capable of redirecting non-	/	tilde.team	70
ihuman visitors to a desired service, i.e. iocaine. Note that	/	tilde.team	70
iin my case, NGINX runs on the host system, it is not	/	tilde.team	70
iconteuneurized, it is managed by a systemd service.	/	tilde.team	70
hiocaine	URL:https://iocaine.madhouse-project.org/	iocaine.madhouse-project.org	443
i	/	tilde.team	70
i## My iocaine configuration	/	tilde.team	70
i	/	tilde.team	70
iI kept the basic configuration to customize the web pages	/	tilde.team	70
igenerated by the tool. I've downloaded three books, Uncle	/	tilde.team	70
iTom's cabin, Lady Chatterley's lover and Brave New World	/	tilde.team	70
iwhose content will be used to generate text. The tool also	/	tilde.team	70
ineeds a word list.	/	tilde.team	70
hUncle Tom's cabin	URL:https://archive.org/details/uncletomscabinta0000stow/mode/2up?ref=ol	archive.org	443
hLady Chatterley's lover	URL:https://archive.org/details/ladychatterleysl0000dhla_o6r7/page/2/mode/2up?ref=ol	archive.org	443
hBrave New World	URL:https://archive.org/details/ost-english-brave_new_world_aldous_huxley	archive.org	443
hword list	URL:https://git.savannah.gnu.org/cgit/miscfiles.git/plain/web2	git.savannah.gnu.org	443
i	/	tilde.team	70
i## My iocaine deployment	/	tilde.team	70
i	/	tilde.team	70
iTo deploy the solution I chose to use Docker Compose with a	/	tilde.team	70
iconfiguration base suggested by the documentation. Below is	/	tilde.team	70
ithe iocaine deployment file.	/	tilde.team	70
i	/	tilde.team	70
iservices:	/	tilde.team	70
i  iocaine:	/	tilde.team	70
i    image: git.madhouse-project.org/iocaine/iocaine:2	/	tilde.team	70
i    container_name: iocaine	/	tilde.team	70
i    ports:	/	tilde.team	70
i      - "127.0.0.1:42069:42069"	/	tilde.team	70
i      - "127.0.0.1:42070:42070"	/	tilde.team	70
i    volumes:	/	tilde.team	70
i      - "./data:/data"	/	tilde.team	70
i    environment:	/	tilde.team	70
i      - IOCAINE__SERVER__BIND="0.0.0.0:42069"	/	tilde.team	70
i      - IOCAINE__SOURCES__WORDS="/data/words.txt"	/	tilde.team	70
i      - IOCAINE__SOURCES__MARKOV=["/data/text1.txt",	/	tilde.team	70
i"/data/text2.txt", "/data/text3.txt"]	/	tilde.team	70
i      - IOCAINE__METRICS__ENABLE=true	/	tilde.team	70
i      - IOCAINE__METRICS__BIND="0.0.0.0:42070"	/	tilde.team	70
i      - IOCAINE__METRICS__LABELS=["Host","UserAgent"]	/	tilde.team	70
i    restart: unless-stopped	/	tilde.team	70
i    networks:	/	tilde.team	70
i      - monitoring_prometheus_net	/	tilde.team	70
i	/	tilde.team	70
inetworks:	/	tilde.team	70
i  monitoring_prometheus_net:	/	tilde.team	70
i    external: true	/	tilde.team	70
i	/	tilde.team	70
iThe monitoring_prometheus_net network is used by Prometheus	/	tilde.team	70
iand Prometheus exporters containers. Applying it to the	/	tilde.team	70
iiocaine container allows Pormetheus to reach the iocaine	/	tilde.team	70
iPrometheus exporter behind port 42070. In this way, we can	/	tilde.team	70
iview the metrics of iocaine via a dashboard in Grafana.	/	tilde.team	70
hiocaine	URL:https://iocaine.madhouse-project.org/	iocaine.madhouse-project.org	443
hiocaine	URL:https://iocaine.madhouse-project.org/	iocaine.madhouse-project.org	443
i	/	tilde.team	70
iThe value of IOCAINE__SOURCES__WORDS corresponds to a file	/	tilde.team	70
iwhich is the list of words previously downloaded and the	/	tilde.team	70
ivalue of IOCAINE__SOURCES__MARKOV represents a list of three	/	tilde.team	70
ifiles which are the aforementioned books.	/	tilde.team	70
i	/	tilde.team	70
i## The robots are stuck	/	tilde.team	70
i	/	tilde.team	70
iThe service is now deployed and the NGINX configuration has	/	tilde.team	70
ibeen updated for the tool and loaded. Now all we have to do	/	tilde.team	70
iis wait to see the first trapped robots.	/	tilde.team	70
i	/	tilde.team	70
